TT OF INDIAN RIVER, INC., d/b/a Mercedes Benz of Melbourne and James C. Dorman, Appellants,
v.
Heidi FORTSON, Appellee. Case No. 5D17-0279 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Fifth District. Opinion filed March 9, 2018 Richard A. Sherman, Sr. and James W. Sherman, of the Law Offices of Richard A. Sherman, P.A., Fort Lauderdale, and Chris Killer and Todd Bohnenstiehl, of the Law Offices of J. Christopher Norris, Orlando, for Appellants. Mark S. Roman and Morgan L. Gaynor, of Roman & Gaynor, Clearwater, Douglas R. Beam, of Douglas R. Beam, P.A., Melbourne, and Celene H. Humphries and Thomas J. Seider, of Brannock & Humphries, Tampa, for Appellee. ON CONFESSION OF ERROR PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to Heidi Fortson's Confession of Error, we reverse the Final Judgment for Costs and remand this matter to the trial court for further proceedings.

REVERSED and REMANDED.

ORFINGER, TORPY, and WALLIS, JJ., concur.
